children.text: The waterproofing in the shower area has not been constructed as required by the Australian Standards. The tiling across the floor has been designed to run continuously through into the shower area under the screen (which does not have a hob or set down) and the required perimeter waterstop to stop moisture migrating out past the shower screens under the tiling has not been installed.
It is a requirement of AS 3740 Waterproofing of Wet Areas within Residential Buildings, clause 3.13.4 Enclosed Showers without Hobs or Set-Downs that

‘At the extremity of the shower area where a shower screen is to be installed, a water stop shall be positioned so that its vertical leg will finish a minimum of 5 mm above the finished floor level (see Figure 3.6); and where the water stop intersects with a wall or is joined, the junction shall be waterproof’ .

The only permissible way this shower detail can be deleted is if the entire wet area floor area (including the area outside the shower) was waterproofed and drained to a separate floor waste, which has not been done in this area. The builder should re-construct these areas to be in accordance with AS 3740.
